Three new #Covid_19 cases were reported in Kolhapur district on Saturday. The total number of active cases stands at seven. Ichalkaranji police have booked ten people for entering the textile town from Belgaum in Karnataka without having valid travel pass.

The Nashik division on Saturday registered first death of a policeman due to #Covid_19 . The policeman got infected during his duty in Malegaon. The 51 year-old man was admitted to the isolation ward on May 2 with mild symptoms and the treatment had begun since then.

The doubling period of positive cases in Malegaon is about 4-5 days as against the national average of about 11 days. State health minister Rajesh Tope admitted to TOI that the rising #Covid_19 cases in Malegaon was 'worrisome.'

Malegaon has recorded a 100% rise in the number of #Covid_19 cases registered in the textile town in just one month. The first five cases were reported in the town on April 7  which increased to 497 on Saturday.

Three new #Covid_19 cases were reported in Kolhapur district on Saturday. The total number of active cases stands at seven. Ichalkaranji police have booked ten people for entering the textile town from Belgaum in Karnataka without having valid travel pass.

The Nashik division on Saturday registered first death of a policeman due to #Covid_19 . The policeman got infected during his duty in Malegaon. The 51 year-old man was admitted to the isolation ward on May 2 with mild symptoms and the treatment had begun since then.

The doubling period of positive cases in Malegaon is about 4-5 days as against the national average of about 11 days. State health minister Rajesh Tope admitted to TOI that the rising #Covid_19 cases in Malegaon was 'worrisome.'

Malegaon has recorded a 100% rise in the number of #Covid_19 cases registered in the textile town in just one month. The first five cases were reported in the town on April 7  which increased to 497 on Saturday.

The binding affinity indicates that this has the possibility of being considered as an antiviral for the novel coronavirus SARS-CoV-2. An affinity of less than -6.0 Kcal/mol is considered good.

We found from docking studies that Aza-Peptide Epoxide (APE) has an affinity of -7.1 Kcal/mol with the 3CL Pro of the novel coronavirus and GRL0617 has an affinity of -7.9 Kcal/mol with the PL Pro of the novel coronavirus.

To ascertain if can use these ligands as antivirals in the novel coronavirus we did a Docking profile of both the ligands with 9 different conformations of the ligands with the SARS-CoV-2 protein model to see if both these ligands can show similar properties.
